aVA "rally cat" appeared in Busch Stadium on Wednesday. It was the sixth inning, with the Cardinals trailing the Kansas City Royals. What happened next is why the ever-superstitious St. Louis fans want the cat to become a regular.\u000a\u000aThe kitty was ejected and then Yadier Molina hit the next pitch for a grand slam home run, giving the Cardinals an 8-5 lead (which also ended up being the game's final score).\u000a\u000aHere's our little hero, the Rally Cat (although the grounds crew guy might say differently). #STLCards pic.twitter.com/OrR2IFAv8d \u2014 FOX Sports Midwest (@FSMidwest) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aThe cat, which headed for the centerfield wall, was retrieved by a member of the Busch Stadium grounds, identified by KMOX as Lucas Hackman. The cat scratched or bit Hackman a couple of times as he was running off the field.\u000a\u000a"I'm not a cat person, but I sure like that one," St. Louis manager Mike Matheny said after the game, per MLB.com. "\u2026 I thought there was a streaker on the field to be honest, but I was happy it was a cat."\u000a\u000aThe cat, nicknamed Yadi, reportedly was seen later being taken from the stadium in a crate, according to Ben Boyd of KMOX Radio.\u000a\u000aLooks like #rallycat will be taken away in that crate #STLCards #Busch pic.twitter.com/C5QsOoNYwn \u2014 Ben Boyd (@BenBoydKMOX) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aEasily my fav moment of Cardinals season. Cat runs on field... Yadi grand slam. #RallyCat pic.twitter.com/S4Zxz7qq7D \u2014 Chris Vernon (@ChrisVernonShow) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aComing soon to ESPN\u000a\u000a30 for 30: Rally Cat pic.twitter.com/AKyeJHMKg8 \u2014 Trevor (@Thuth97) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aRally Cat is now being chanted at Busch....#STLCards \u2014 Brian Stull (@StullySTL) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aBut the kid who got maimed by #rallycat at Busch Stadium gets my vote for hero of the night. \u2014 Peter Fleischer (@Peter_Fleischer) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aLook out Cardinal Nation!!!! RALLY CAT!!! #12in17 \u2014 Meghan Boschert (@MeggoBoschert) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aYadi found a new fan club on social media.
