aVTravel deals and discounts for different services and products are some of the benefits AARP members enjoy. They also satisfy their appetites and save money at many AARP-friendly restaurants.\u000a\u000aPeople can start receiving these benefits after joining AARP. Memberships are available as soon as you reach age 50. Members often get to eat at their favorite restaurants with special treatment. Many restaurants have joined in to offer membership discounts. You might find a dining place you love by checking out the AARP site for updated information on restaurant deals and other benefits.\u000a\u000aALERT: 'Real and Present Danger' \u2013 Get the Emergency Radio Now!\u000a\u000aA membership card provides you with a variety of choices, no matter what your taste. Here are eight of the most AARP-friendly restaurants:\u000a\u000a1. Denny\u2019s \u2014 Seniors often take advantage of the delicious meals at Denny\u2019s for breakfast, lunch, or dinner. AARP members save 15 percent when eating at this popular restaurant.\u000a\u000a\u200b2. Saltgrass Steak House \u2014 Show an AARP membership card and save 10 percent on food and non-alcoholic drinks. Enjoy fresh breads, salads, soups, and desserts as well as great steaks.\u000a\u000a\u200b3. Outback Steakhouse \u2014 Members receive 10 percent off on meals for lunch or dinner. Along with steaks, Outback offers chicken, seafood, and side orders.\u000a\u000a\u200b4. Bonefish Grill \u2014 Grilled fish and seafood specialties, such as Chilean sea bass and salmon, are among the delicacies offered with soups and greens. AARP members save 10 percent on their entire dining bill, according to EatDrinkDeals.\u000a\u000aIMPORTANT: Gingrich and Reagan Video Goes Viral. See It Now\u000a\u000a\u200b5. Bubba Gump Shrimp \u2014 Members receive 10-percent discounts on fresh seafood dinners. Take advantage of the restaurant and market that was inspired by the 1994 movie Forrest Gump.\u000a\u000a6. Carrabba\u2019s Italian Grill \u2014 Appetizers, soups, and salads are just starters. Entres include steaks, chicken, pork, veal, seafood, and pasta. AARP members save 10 percent at participating locations, according to the Senior List.\u000a\u000a\u200b7. Chart House \u2014 The restaurant is an ideal dining experience for people who love steaks and fresh food with beautiful views. Seniors get 10 percent off with an AARP membership.\u000a\u000a8. Oceanaire Seafood Room \u2014 One of the top seafood restaurants in the country, Oceanaire boasts of having the freshest seafood flown in daily. AARP members receive 10 percent off food and non-alcoholic beverages.\u000a\u000aTIP: How to Retire Comfortably on $2,000
