aVA Cheetos-themed restaurant is opening in New York City with celebrity chef Anne Burrell making the creations.\u000a\u000aThe Spotted Cheetah will be open for just three days, from Aug. 15 to 17, with three-course meals featuring all different kinds of Cheetos, Business Insider reported. The pop-up eatery was already taking reservations Tuesday and selling out, with BI reporting it could not find an open Tuesday (Aug. 15) time slot when it tried.\u000a\u000aSome of the culinary creations available at the fine dining establishment include Cheetos Crusted Fried Pickles, Spicy Cheetos Nachos, and Cheetos Sweetos Crusted Cheesecake.\u000a\u000aOther menu items include Cheetos Grilled Cheese and Tomato Soup, Cheetos Meatballs, Flamin\u2019 Hot Limon Chicken Tacos, and Cheetos Sweetos Apple Crepe, BI reported.\u000a\u000aBurrell is a Food Network staple, starring on shows such as \u201cWorst Cooks in America\u201d and \u201cSecrets of a Restaurant Chef.\u201d\u000a\u000a\u201cAs a long-time Cheetos fan, I\u2019m thrilled to join forces with a snack brand that is truly an iconic American staple,\u201d Burrell said in a news release, CNN Money reported. \u201cI had so much fun curating this specially crafted, one-of-a-kind menu for the first Cheetos restaurant \u2014 I can\u2019t wait to see guests\u2019 reactions!\u201d\u000a\u000a"The Spotted Cheetah is a fun and delicious way for Cheetos to celebrate a variety of favorite flavors in an upscale and playful culinary setting that will wow our guests," Senior Director of Marketing at Frito-Lay Ryan Matiyow said, CNN Money reported.\u000a\u000aBurger King currently offers Mac n\u2019 Cheetos on its menu, and Taco Bell offers Cheetos quesadillas, but this is the first time an entire menu has been based on the food, CNN Money reported. A cookbook with recipes for the menu items will be sold online.\u000a\u000aCheetos fans on Twitter were beyond excited about the restaurant.\u000a\u000aI usually prefer mine straight from the bag but all of that looks delicious! \u2014 tammi mochida (@chichimochida) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aI'll do whatever it takes to get off the waitlist for the first day of your pop-up. I'll dress like Chester if I have too!!!! \u2014 Matt Lugo (@WWMLD) August 8, 2017
