aVPresident Donald Trump followed up on recent tweets in which he criticized Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell, with a tweet encouraging McConnell to take action on repeal and replacement of Obamacare and other priorities.\u000a\u000aMitch, get back to work and put Repeal & Replace, Tax Reform & Cuts and a great Infrastructure Bill on my desk for signing. You can do it! \u2014 Donald J. Trump (@realDonaldTrump) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aMcConnell has "screamed repeal and replace for 7 years" about Obamacare, according to Trump in a Thursday morning tweet.\u000a\u000aOn Wednesday, Trump began tweeting criticism of McConnell after the Senate leader said that the president had "excessive expectations" about getting his agenda accomplished.
