aVPresident Donald Trump's base of core voters is stronger than it was before despite polls that show declining approval ratings after his first 200 days in office, author and attorney Alan Dershowitz said Tuesday.\u000a\u000aDuring an appearance on Newsmax TV's "America Talks Live," Dershowitz told host Miranda Khan the poll numbers are somewhat deceiving.\u000a\u000a"I think his real base, which has always been in the 30s, is stronger than ever," Dershowitz said. "That is people who strongly support him, even more strongly support him. So, if you voted by the strength of convictions, he'd do very well."\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-Verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator does not have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2013 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we will connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2013 Click Here Now\u000a\u000aDershowitz noted Trump is losing support among people who were not that excited to vote for him last November.\u000a\u000a"Where he's losing is people who voted for him but weren't that enthusiastic," Dershowitz said. "People who said let's give him a shot, he's promising change, he's promising something different, and now they're a little bit disappointed."
