aVA sketch of Taylor Swift in a Denver federal court this week during a sexual assault trial closed to the press is generating Twitter buzz because people say the unflattering portrait looks nothing like her.\u000a\u000aThe trial is because of a lawsuit Swift filed against Denver DJ David Mueller alleging he groped her during a 2013 meet-and-greet. Mueller denies groping the megastar and has countersued her because he lost his job after her suit went public.\u000a\u000aWith the press kept out of the courtroom, the artist\u2019s sketches are the only window into the goings-on, but fans have been vocally critical of the way Swift is being portrayed.\u000a\u000aTwitter has exploded with jokes and snarky comments about the sketch.\u000a\u000aI see the person who designed the Emma Watson Belle doll is now a courtroom sketch artist for Taylor Swift's trial #taylorswifttrial #smh \u2014 Ally Reid (@ashallann) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000aI think it's safe to say the courtroom sketch artist is a Katy Perry fan #TaylorSwiftTrial pic.twitter.com/PHUpuZLsez \u2014 Sara Weber (@sarapweber) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aHaha exactly. Wow did they make a beautiful girl look horrible. \u2014 Banana (@alana_banana) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000aHow long before Taylor Swift sues this courtroom sketch artist? https://t.co/1UUpVMcoFt pic.twitter.com/njfArypyKi \u2014 Dorsey (@dorseyshaw) August 8, 2017\u000a\u000aAccording to TMZ, Swift is only asking for $1 in the civil lawsuit, saying that it\u2019s about the principle of the matter, not the money, and that she wants to stop the groping from happening to anyone else.
