aVA Sachem East High School football player died after a freak accident during offseason training when a log fell on his head.\u000a\u000aJoshua Mileto, 16, was participating in a drill Thursday morning at the Farmingville, New York school, that involved carrying a log overhead, Fox 5 New York reported.\u000a\u000aMileto, who was scheduled to graduate in 2019, was pronounced dead at Stony Brook University Hospital, the station noted.\u000a\u000aSuffolk County Police are investigating the death, ABC News reported.\u000a\u000a"The district is devastated by this horrific accident and words cannot express the grief we feel as a school community," Superintendent Kenneth Graham said in a statement. "We extend our deepest condolences to the student's family and friends during this terribly difficult time."\u000a\u000aThe district made a crisis intervention team and support services available to students and staff.\u000a\u000aCommunity members posted about the incident on Facebook, The New York Daily News noted, quoting Anita Raum, whose son witnessed the accident saying, "This is beyond the WORST thing that could happen to our Football family and community. \u2026 Please keep this family in your prayers and all of his football brothers and coaches that are suffering so deeply. Our Sachem Community is hurting over this tragic loss."\u000a\u000aMileto was remembered on Twitter.\u000a\u000aRest easy Joshua Mileto \U0001f64f\U0001f3fe\U0001f3c8 \u2014 fetty_brags (@thehumble_kb) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000aA wiki in memory https://t.co/UlAfIw7v7h \u2014 NavinVeth (@NavV96) August 10, 2017
