aVA Walnut gun display with the back-to-school promotional sign "Own the school year like a hero" on it led to an apology from the retail giant and confusion over how the signed ended up on the display in the first place.\u000a\u000aThe photo of the back-to-school sign over the gun display went viral this week, promoting the response from Walmart.\u000a\u000aOh @Walmart \U0001f926\U0001f3fc\u200d\u2642\ufe0f pic.twitter.com/SLdROB4KYF \u2014 Ismail Kidd Noorzai (@ismailkidd) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000aYes, Walmart had a \u201cBack to School\u201d sign on a rack of guns. pic.twitter.com/oLPESt5yL2 \u2014 Gaslighting A Nation (@Gaslit_Nation) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000ai fear a world where walmart sells guns anyway... but this... poor signage choice \u2014 Kelsey (@Kelseycoz) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000aIn all their tone-deafness I'm surprised they didn't give away free guns as a way to say sorry. \u2014 Sue.Cee (@suecee2011) August 10, 2017\u000a\u000a"What's seen in this photograph would never be acceptable in our stores," Charles Crowson, a spokesman for Walmart, told The Washington Post. "We regret this situation and are looking into how it could have happened."\u000a\u000aCrowson told the Post that Walmart was trying to find what store the photo was taken at and if the sign was placed on the display by an employee or a shopper.\u000a\u000aLeeanna May told the Post she took the photo while shopping at an Evansville, Indiana, Walmart with her husband.\u000a\u000a"We have already lost so many innocent lives to guns," May told the Post.\u000a\u000aCrowson told CNNMoney that the company thought it had identified the store and that the sign had been removed, but that was a mistake.\u000a\u000aWalmart posted tweets about the sign Wednesday.\u000a\u000aWe hear you. \U0001f61e This was horrible and we removed the sign as soon as we found out. -Vik \u2014 Walmart (@Walmart) August 9, 2017
