aVThe socials are all a-Twitter today over Google\u2019s sacking of James Damore over his leaked \u201cmanifesto\u201d criticizing the company for its blatant leftist bias. In the past few hours every time I glance up at my Twitter feed there are several hundred new tweets flooding in that blast the company for confirming what we all knew: Google is the most radically leftist company in the world today.\u000a\u000aTitled \u201cGoogle\u2019s Ideological Echo Chamber,\u201d Damore\u2019s document takes the Mountain View behemoth to task for an intrinsic leftist political bias that equates freedom from offense with psychological safety. He laments the shaming and silencing of dissenting opinions at Google as leading to \u201can ideological echo chamber where some ideas are too sacred to be honestly discussed.\u201d\u000a\u000aWhat\u2019s surprising about Damore\u2019s manifesto (and yes as a woman I was steeled myself to be outraged given the media indignation) is just how profoundly non-threatening it is. Damore admits that bias and sexism exist, writes that he has no patience for stereotypes, and strongly believes in diversity and inclusion.\u000a\u000aDo I agree with everything he wrote? Certainly not. His argument that different personality traits between the sexes may in part explain why there aren\u2019t more women in tech is interesting and may have some kernels of truth to it, but it\u2019s clumsy and not very well-thought out.\u000a\u000aWithout wading further into the gender-equality swamp however, what really struck me was the unhinged reaction of his (now former) colleagues. Just Damore\u2019s mild dissent from Google\u2019s leftist orthodoxy caused a Pavlovian response as Googlers took to their fainting couches. One wrote that the manifesto was \u201cputting Googler\u2019s physical safety at risk.\u201d Other female Googlers (Googlettes?) claimed they were so upset by the contents that they simply couldn\u2019t come to work, thus kind of validating Damore\u2019s clumsy point no?\u000a\u000aIn an interesting twist, the internal nonsense at Google confirms months of suspicion among those of us on the right that the company is blocking, censoring, and blacklisting conservatives online.\u000a\u000aLet me explain: Breitbart\u2019s Allum Bokhari published a fascinating interview today with \u201cHal\u201d an anonymous Googler who confirms that the company\u2019s employees routinely create internal \u201cwrongthink\u201d blacklists to destroy the careers of their colleagues who don\u2019t toe the line with Google\u2019s accepted SJW (social justice warrior) groupthink:\u000a\u000a"Several managers have openly admitted to keeping blacklists of the employees in question, and preventing them from seeking work at other companies. There have been numerous cases in which social justice activists coordinated attempts to sabotage other employees\u2019 performance reviews for expressing a different opinion. These have been raised to the Senior VP level, with no action taken whatsoever."\u000a\u000aThese are the very same engineers who tweak Google\u2019s algorithms on a daily basis. Now ask yourself: Is it reasonable to believe that Google employees who keep internal blacklists of wrongthinkers, sabotage their performance reviews, and even prevent them from finding work at other companies aren\u2019t sneaking their leftist political biases into Google\u2019s completely non-transparent search algorithms? Can we take Google at face value when it claims that blocking outspoken SJW critic Jordan Peterson\u2019s YouTube account was simply a \u201cmistake\u201d? Or that the hundreds of similar examples at other lefty Silicon Valley companies aren\u2019t deliberate attempts to sabotage conservative voices online?\u000a\u000aAs Free Our Internet has warned repeatedly, the day of reckoning for Silicon Valley is coming, and the Damore firing may be the inflection point. New right personality Mike Cernovich announced just this morning plans for a \u201cfreedom rally\u201d outside of Google\u2019s headquarters to protest its blatant censorship of conservatives on YouTube.\u000a\u000aIronically, at the same time Google pinky swears that despite all of the mounting evidence, it would never, ever censor conservatives online, it\u2019s cynically using the same \u201ccensorship\u201d argument to fight new sex trafficking legislation to prosecute websites like Backpage that knowingly facilitate the buying and selling of young girls for sex.\u000a\u000aA group called Consumer Watchdog has all of the gory details here about how the company funded dozens of activist groups, professors, and legal scholars to support Backpage\u2019s legal defense to fight lawsuits filed by underage girls who had been bought and sold like cattle through Backpage\u2019s adult personals section, some hundreds of times.\u000a\u000aAnti-sex trafficking groups are enraged, with groups like the National Center on Sexual Exploitation blasting the company as \u201ccaring more about its bottom line than the victims of serial rape for profit.\u201d\u000a\u000aAgainst this backdrop, an interesting Business Insider story last week kind of puts an exclamation point on the growing outrage over Google\u2019s complete disconnect from the rest of America. The story reported on a new restaurant that Google\u2019s elites are flocking to in Silicon Valley where they casually dine on\u2026 gold-flecked steak.\u000a\u000aChristie-Lee McNally is the founder of Free Our Internet. She was the Maine Statewide Director for Donald J. Trump for President in 2016, is a concealed weapons permit holder, and a USAW Certified Olympic Lifting Coach. To read more of her reports \u2014 Click Here Now.
