aVMilwaukee County Sheriff David Clarke on Tuesday praised President Donald Trump for his pledge to step up enforcement to combat the opioid crisis.\u000a\u000a"It's a big voice and when the president talks, as you know, people listen," he told Rita Cosby, guest host of "The Schnitt Show," on NewsmaxTV.\u000a\u000a"They'll bring federal resources now to this epidemic, really, this horrible scourge that's been sweeping the country. Many deaths, as you know, but you've got to have a multi-pronged approach. I think President Trump understands that we have to look at how we're prosecuting heroin dealers and what I'm seeing right now, which I'm railing about back here in Milwaukee, Wis. is treating heroin dealers just like any other dealer."\u000a\u000aImportant: Newsmax TV is available on DirecTV Ch. 349, U-Verse 1220, and FiOS 615. If your cable operator does not have Newsmax TV just call and ask them to put us on \u2013 Call toll-free 1-844-500-6397 and we will connect you right away to your cable operator!\u000a\u000aFor more places to Find Newsmax TV \u2013 Click Here Now\u000a\u000aTrump held a briefing on the matter at his private golf course in Bedminster, N.J., telling reporters "we will fight this deadly epidemic and the United States will win." The president vowed to work with health professionals and law enforcement and promised he would "be bringing [federal drug prosecutions] up rapidly."\u000a\u000aClarke said heroin dealers need to be dealt a tougher sentence.\u000a\u000a"A dealer in marijuana, a dealer in small possession amounts of cocaine and they're throwing them in with that, they're using all of these soft, if you will, prosecution methods to deal with heroin dealers. These guys are peddling poison," he said.
