aVHitting the links has never been the same since golf lovers have been blessed with smartphone apps. They can improve their game by using something they nearly always have with them.\u000a\u000aMobile apps have become one of the most popular tools to improve function, including golf performance. Golfers can develop new strategies by getting information from programs that analyze their particular techniques and suggest improved methods.\u000a\u000aURGENT:\u000a\u000aWho's The Greatest Golfer Of All Time? Vote Now\u000a\u000aConsider using one or more of these six smartphone golf apps to improve your game:\u000a\u000a1. Golf GPS Rangefinder & Scoring \u2014 Golf enthusiasts might love this app for the images it has of nearly every golf course in the world, according to WebAppRater. Users have access to website data to track their games. There is also a digital scorecard included.\u000a\u000a\u200b2. V1 Golf \u2014 The app helps improve your golf swing for better accuracy at hitting the ball to the right spot. The video helps fine-tune a golfer\u2019s basic skills by recording a player\u2019s swing and comparing it with more than 50 templates from pro golfers.\u000a\u000a3. Tiger Woods: My Swing \u2014 What better way to improve a swing than taking lessons from one of the masters of the game! In this app, players also record videos of their own swing and compare it to Tiger\u2019s style in the quest to improve their game, power and accuracy.\u000a\u000aPOLL:\u000a\u000a4. GAME Golf \u2014 The system includes chips that clip to a player\u2019s golf clubs and one to your belt. By touching the chip on the belt before each swing, the app records your positions to analyze distances, movements, and inclinations. It\u2019s like having a PGA Tour system following and tracking you, notes Golf Academy of America. The app is free, but clip devices cost about $199.\u000a\u000a\u200b5. My Pro to Go \u2014 Here\u2019s something that lets a pro give you advice on your swing. GolfTec-certified instructors at My Pro to Go look at videos you take of your swing. Players get personalized instruction. This app is also free, but the valuable lesson plans start at $39.\u000a\u000a6. Golf Channel Mobile \u2014 The official application of the Golf Channel was named one of the 10 best golf apps for Android by Android Authority. Along with tips from experts and advice for fantasy golf, the free app includes golf news, analysis, and profiles of players.\u000a\u000aVOTE:\u000a\u000aWho Is The Best Golfer?
