aVA Democratic candidate for an Arizona state Senate seat said that pornographic images posted on his Twitter account were the result of hacking.\u000a\u000a"Darn those Russians!" candidate Steve Weichert said in a tweet in response to the hacking.\u000a\u000aMy apologies to anyone who may have received a rather lewd tweet from me this morning. My account was hacked. (Darn those Russians!) \u2014 Steve Weichert (@SteveWeichert) August 7, 2017\u000a\u000aThe candidate was taking his daughters to school when he found out about the pornographic tweets, Weichert said to ABC15.\u000a\u000a"All of a sudden, I just felt my phone blowing up. Somebody sent me a text saying, 'What are you doing?' and I'm like 'What? What are you talking about?'"\u000a\u000a"It was a bad Monday," Weichert said.\u000a\u000aLater, Weichert sent follow-up tweets, saying that he was joking about Russians being involved in the hack.\u000a\u000aHonestly, I made a (bad) joke about it, but I don't think this was politically motivated at all - by Russians or my opponent. \u2014 Steve Weichert (@SteveWeichert) August 9, 2017\u000a\u000aIn case anyone is curious, "I was protecting my Twitter account from an unauthorized porn avalanche" is not the best excuse for being late. \u2014 Steve Weichert (@SteveWeichert) August 7, 2017\u000a\u000aHe also compared the porn tweets to a scene from "I Love Lucy."
